Question:- scnerio based Constructors learning.

We want to store the data of 3 movies

You have to store the following data of each movies.

A.  Batman 1:
Rating: 8
Money Collection: 200,000
Profit: 5000
Lead Actor: John
Lead Actress: Disha

B.  Batman 2:
Rating: 9
Money Collection: 500,000
Profit: 8000
Lead Actor: Akshay
Lead Actress: Anushka

C.  Batman 3:
Rating: 10
Money Collection: 700,000
Profit: 6000
Lead Actor: Ajay
Lead Actress: Deepika 
Make a class named movies which stores the appropriate properties as given above.

Make a parameterized constructor which stores all the properties of the objects.

Now make 3 objects named batman1 batman2 and batman3 and for its properties assign the values as written above by using a parameterized constructor.

First print the below details of the Batman 1 movie such that each detail is printed in a separate line.

Rating of the movie,
Money Collection of the movie,
Profit of the movie,
Lead Actor of the movie,    
Lead Actress of the movie.
Similarly, from the next line, print the details of the movie Batman 2 and after that print the details of the movie Batman 3.

Input Format

No input will be given.

Constraints

No Constraints are there.

Output Format

Print the properties of the object Batman4 but using the proper concepts of object oriented programming language.

9
700000
9000
Jack
Alia
Sample Output 0

8
200000
5000
John
Disha
9
500000
8000
Akshay
Anushka
10
700000
6000
Ajay
Deepika

//Solutions.........
import java.io.*;
import java.util.*;
  class Movie {
     int rating;
     long money;
     long profit;
       String actor;
      String actress;
      
      Movie(int rating,long money,long profit,String actor,String actress) {
          this.rating=rating;
          this.money=money;
          this.profit=profit;
          this.actor=actor;
          this.actress=actress;
      }
  }

public class Solution {
    public static void main(String[] args) {
        Movie m1=new  Movie(8,200000,5000,"John","Disha");
        Movie m2=new Movie(9,500000,8000,"Akshay","Anushka");
        Movie m3=new Movie(10,700000,6000,"Ajay","Deepika");
         
        
        System.out.println(m1.rating);
        System.out.println(m1.money);
        System.out.println(m1.profit);
        System.out.println(m1.actor);
        System.out.println(m1.actress);
        
        System.out.println(m2.rating);
        System.out.println(m2.money);
        System.out.println(m2.profit);
        System.out.println(m2.actor);
        System.out.println(m2.actress);
        
        System.out.println(m3.rating);
        System.out.println(m3.money);
        System.out.println(m3.profit);
        System.out.println(m3.actor);
        System.out.println(m3.actress);
    }
}
